      "description": "The model is applicable within the following bounded conditions: axial compressive load 0–2500 N; bending moment 0–25 N·m; screw outer diameter 7.3–7.7 mm (nominal 7.5 mm, tolerance ±0.2 mm); rod diameter 5.4–5.6 mm; polyaxial head angulation 0–15°; crosshead displacement rate 5 mm/min ±0.5 mm/min per ASTM F1717; ambient temperature 20–25 °C; titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V ELI material (UTS 930–970 MPa, yield 860–900 MPa). Extrapolation beyond these bounds is not supported by the validation evidence."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct applicability domain",
      "description": "This credibility assessment applies exclusively to non-cannulated solid-core pedicle screws with a nominal 7.5 mm outer diameter fabricated from Ti-6Al-4V ELI, tested in the ASTM F1717 two-screw-rod construct configuration. It does not apply to cannulated variants, screws outside the 7.3–7.7 mm diameter band, alternative alloys (e.g., CoCr, PEEK), or dynamic/fatigue loading regimes. Spinal level is limited to thoracolumbar (T10–L5) for which the F1717 geometry is representative."
    }
  },
